The UN-sponsored climate conference, which has so far been challenged positions and mutual recriminations, drew renewed attention on Friday with the release of a document that foresees ambitious reductions in greenhouse gases over the next 40 years, with industrialized nations carrying most of the burden on their shoulders in the short term.
